comment:
* The DOMStringList interface provides the abstraction of an * ordered collection of DOMString values, without defining or * constraining how this collection is implemented. The items in the * DOMStringList are accessible via an integral index, starting * from 0. *

See also the Document Object Model (DOM) Level 3 Core Specification. * @since DOM Level 3

methods.name: public String item(int index)
methods.comment: * Returns the indexth item in the collection. If * index is greater than or equal to the number of * DOMStrings in the list, this returns null. * @param index Index into the collection. * @return The DOMString at the indexth * position in the DOMStringList, or null if * that is not a valid index.

methods.name: public int getLength()
methods.comment: * The number of DOMStrings in the list. The range of valid * child node indices is 0 to length-1 inclusive.

methods.name: public boolean contains(String str)
methods.comment: * Test if a string is part of this DOMStringList. * @param str The string to look for. * @return true if the string has been found, * false otherwise.
